Described as "the most reliable phone ever made", the Nokia 3310 will be relaunched on their 26 February.&nbsp; According to Independent&nbsp;the phone will be revealed at Mobile World Congress in Barcelona.&nbsp; The new Nokia 3310 will be sold for for 59 EUR, which is R810.07.&nbsp; According to Wired The Finnish manufacturer with rights to the Nokia brand will announce four new phones including the Nokia 6.&nbsp; The Nokia 3310 is famously known for it's long battery life and built in game called Snake.